For boat stations, channel (Chnl) and shoal (Shl) designations refer to whether the station is relatively deep or
shallow. Directions are indicated by single letters without periods following. Distances and directions are
approximate. Two latitude/longitudes indicate that tow was either made between the locations or
started at a given location at a given tide; distinctions are made in the description.
